		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">There shouldn't be an inherent input lag in emulators like MAME.</div><br />Not in MAME, but in Direct3D when you enable vsync. This is an objective fact that I measured and can be reconstructed by anybody. (If you want to know more, just ask.)<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also, don't use triple buffering, only double buffering. Triple buffering can add 1 frame of lag (it's an option because it can increase performance at the cost of 1 frame of latency).</div><br />I don't think MAME offers double buffering. But I use neither, only vsync. And vsync in fullscreen in Direct3D produces input lag.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
