		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Arcade-perfect &quot;Pac-Man&quot; version?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The original PacMan arcade machine was Z80-based, so I'd arbitrarily guess that machines that had more in common with that (e.g. SMS, Spectrum) have a better chance of duplicating the mechanics, due to being able to reuse larger portions of the original code.<br /></div>You're kidding me, right?<br /></div>Why would I jest? A source code port has a better chance of being correct than one that <em>necessarily</em> requires a rewrite.<br />Similarly, a port to a machine that has a tilemap and sprites is more likely to be correct than one that only has a tilemap, which is why you're complaining about the Spectrum.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
